OL,3,CPolice behaved 'appropriately' before
OL,4,Cboy's fatal e-bike crash
OL,6,FThe Independent Office for Police
OL,7,FConduct (IOPC) launched an
OL,8,Finvestigation after it received a
OL,9,Fmandatory referral from Greater
OL,10,FManchester Police.
OL,12,FIts investigation found that although
OL,13,Fthe police presence may have affected
OL,14,Fthe manner of Saul's riding, there was
OL,15,Fno indication any officer had behaved
OL,16,Fin a manner that would justify the
OL,17,Fbringing of disciplinary proceedings
OL,18,For had committed a criminal offence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
